parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Design Flaw in Engine Oiling System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A design flaw in the engine oiling system can cause premature wear of bearings, rod bolts, and other engine components, leading to engine failure, loss of power, and potential accidents.
The sudden failure of the Continental tire sidewall can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, damage, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The tire suddenly loses air pressure
the tire separates from the wheel at the bead
the tire is attached only to the outside rim edge

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Intermediate Main Shaft (IMS) can cause catastrophic engine failure, leading to a loss of power, overheating, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
